{
  "stem": "3848.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "When the war started in '39 and Russia took a part of Poland and most of the [NON-ENGLISH] they called them at the time, from the Polish side-- from the German side of Poland were running towards our city of Rowne and Lutsk and other cities in Volhynia where I remember we put them up--",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--in the houses.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Jews that were running away.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were asked by the Russians what they want to do, whether they want to go back to Germany to their part of Poland, or would they like to go to Russia?",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And most of them said, yes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We would like to go back home.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And just because of that, the Russian government sent them away one day to Siberia.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My personal experiences-- in 1939, when the Russians came in, I learned the language of Russian.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then, they opened up a school, which was called [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In Russian, it's called [RUSSIAN], where you learn a trade while you're learning other things.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's like a trade school.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "After six months, I graduated that school.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I learned, in the town of Zdolbuniv, which is 12 kilometers from Rowne, to work on a locomotive.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They call it locomotive engineering.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And on the railroad, other things, whatever is involved for the railroad.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When I graduated sometime in 1941-- I'm sorry, that was in 1940-- I was sent to a town, which was called Kamionka Strumilowa.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The town is about 28 kilometers from Lvov on the border-- the new border-- of Germany.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I worked on that station until the war started in 1941, June the  22nd.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, actually the war-- the war was started in '39.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But in '41 is when the Germans attacked Russia.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
